text: Center of the village Hoogerheide is a village in the municipality of Woensdrecht, North Brabant, Netherlands. The name "Hoogerheide" means "High Heath" in English. The Grand Prix Adri van der Poel cyclo-cross race is held annually in Hoogerheide. ==External links== * History of Hoogerheide Category:Populated places in North Brabant Category:Woensdrecht
title: Hoogerheide
